SIMPLE: water_gall
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Water gall
<hw>Wa"ter gall`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <sn>1.</sn> <def>A cavity made in
the earth by a torrent of water; a washout.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A watery appearance in the sky, accompanying the
rainbow; a secondary or broken rainbow.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>These <qex>water galls</qex>, in her dim element,⟦br⟧
Foretell new storms to those already spent.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>False good news are [is] always produced by true good, like the
<qex>water gall</qex> by the rainbow.</q>
<rj><qau>Walpole.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Water gang</ent>⟦br⟧
